7. KEY EDGE CASES & RISK MITIGATION
7.1 Voice Edge Cases
Jarvis hears its own TTS output → 3-second microphone cooldown after speech begins. Single speaker rule: if frontend is speaking, backend does not.
Background noise triggers wake word → Confidence threshold: only wake if speech recognition confidence > 0.7
User pauses mid-sentence → 2-second silence threshold before treating as end of utterance
User says 'stop' mid-sentence normally → only trigger stop if 'stop' is standalone word (surrounded by silence or punctuation)
Two people speaking at once → first recognized voice wins. Queue second command.
Whisper misunderstands technical terms → allow user to spell out critical commands: 'j-a-r-v-i-s'

7.2 System Edge Cases
C: drive reaches 100% full → Jarvis stops saving to C: immediately, warns RED, suggests moving files to E:
Ollama crashes mid-response → detect timeout after 30s, switch to Gemini, tell user 'Local AI unavailable, using cloud fallback'
Internet goes down mid-session → switch all services to offline mode, notify once, continue with local Ollama
8GB RAM fully consumed → reduce polling intervals, stop background tasks, notify RED, offer to kill processes
E: drive disconnected (portable HDD unplugged) → gracefully disable vault/skill features, log warning, restore when reconnected

7.3 Security Edge Cases
